      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@user515655 - The language defines a <code>--</code> operator (actually, two of them, along with two <code>++</code> operators), but doesn&#39;t define a <code>!!</code> operator. If you want <code>-(-(integer))</code> you can use white space between the two <code>-</code> characters. But <code>!!</code> parses as two <code>!</code> operators regardless of white space."
