    "question_id" : 224311,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This answer came up when searching for \"java invert boolean function\". The example below will prevent certain static analysis tools from failing builds due to branching logic. This is useful if you need to invert a boolean and haven't built out comprehensive unit tests ;)</p>\n\n<pre><code>Boolean.valueOf(aBool).equals(false)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or alternatively:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Boolean.FALSE.equals(aBool)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or </p>\n\n<pre><code>Boolean.FALSE::equals\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
